reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 6, 2023
reviews.reviewText: They are not addictive like some. Somewhat odd flavor and texture but my leg cramp issues disappeared. Electrolyte supplement drink powders were not fixing the problem during the hot summer days

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 17, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The taste and texture were satisfying in my opinion. Kinda reminded me of a fruit roll up and a Starburst. I did buy these because of the particular list of vitamins. I felt healthy and energized, I didn't notice any negative side effects

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars One kid liked the other didn't
reviews.reviewText: I ordered this to try and support my child with ADHD...of course she is the one that didn't like it. The taste is tart and the texture is not like a gummy, it is a combination of crumbly and chewy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 2, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Does not have a weird taste like people have said. I tried one to know what I was giving my kids. It has a “now & later” candy texture- it’s a bit hard at first but gets easier to chew. Does leave a very tiny gritty feel on your teeth after, but once you take a drink that does away. My kids are excited to take them in the morning because it’s like “eating candy for breakfast”. Will definitely continue to keep buying as they need the extra minerals!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 7, 2023
reviews.reviewText: My kids really like the taste of these. I’ve always heard that magnesium is good for kids with ADHD, and both of my kids are diagnosed, so I thought we would check these out. The thing is as a parent you can’t really know if it’s making that much of a difference because there are so many variables in their diet and changes in their hormones and sleep, etc. but I figured it couldn’t hurt. We loved them!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Kids aged 3, 6 and 8 all said they tasted bad and refused to take them.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 29, 2020
reviews.reviewText: These are very sweet with a slight vitamin taste that is certainly tolerable but I can see why children may not like them. The taste doesn’t linger and it disappears after a few sips of coffee. I can’t swallow pills and I wanted a multivitamin that included minerals so it is what it is. This company is one of the only ones I found in a chewable that includes them. I tried liquid dropper type vitamins to avoid sugars and the one I tried made my mouth sour for a while and tainted the taste of anything I ate or drank after it. So these are my best option if I am going to be vigilant in taking a supplement.So beyond my personal opinion I am giving the company five stars because it’s a nicely packaged product and good quality and arrived in perfect condition.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024
reviews.reviewText: These have a horrible taste. My kid wouldn’t eat them and spit them out. I tried one and it made me gag. I do not recommend!
The price in Amazon is better than iherb. My twin boys love this vitamins very much that nutritionize them.
